org.apache.poi.ss.formula.ptg

Class ArrayPtg

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.poi.ss.formula.ptg.Ptg
      • org.apache.poi.ss.formula.ptg.ArrayPtg
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Duplicatable, GenericRecord 

    public final class ArrayPtg
extends Ptg
    ArrayPtg - handles arrays The ArrayPtg is a little weird, the size of the Ptg when parsing initially only includes the Ptg sid and the reserved bytes. The next Ptg in the expression then follows. It is only after the "size" of all the Ptgs is met, that the ArrayPtg data is actually held after this. So Ptg.createParsedExpression keeps track of the number of ArrayPtg elements and need to parse the data upto the FORMULA record size.(${t_ad6e0df5008d41c8a574192b20e76cb6})
